20 TRAFFICKING AREA AWARDS.
21
22 WHEREAS, the Division of Arkansas State Police's Interstate Criminal
23 Patrol team received multiple accolades at the Gulf Coast High Intensity Drug
24 Trafficking Area Awards held on April 1, 2025, in Biloxi, Mississippi; and
25
26 WHEREAS, the Division of Arkansas State Police's Interstate Criminal
27 Patrol team was recognized as the 2024 Agency of the Year because of
28 successful seizure of illegal narcotics with a street value of thirty-two
29 million, two hundred fifty thousand, four hundred seventy-six dollars
30 ($32,250,476), confiscation of twenty-five (25) vehicles, and recovery of
31 four million, one hundred thousand dollars ($4,100,000) in cash; and
32
33 WHEREAS, Trooper Ana Escamilla of the Division of Arkansas State
34 Police's Interstate Criminal Patrol team was named 2024 Officer of the Year
35 for netting twenty-one (21) drug seizures and seven (7) currency seizures
36 amounting to a combined street value of four million, nine hundred eighty-
