5 WHEREAS, Corporal Chris Short of the Division of Arkansas State
6 Police's Interstate Criminal Patrol team was recognized for the 2024 Largest
7 Cash Seizure, which totaled eight hundred thirteen thousand, four hundred
8 ninety dollars ($813,490) and was made during a single traffic stop in
9 Crawford County, Arkansas; and
10
11 WHEREAS, the Division of Arkansas State Police's Interstate Criminal
12 Patrol team was also recognized in 2022 and 2023 as the Team of the Year, and
13 this was the third consecutive year a team member was named Officer of the
14 Year; and
15
16 WHEREAS, Director of the Division of Arkansas State Police Colonel Mike
17 Hagar said of the wins, "I am extremely proud of the exemplary work our
18 troopers assigned to the ICP teams perform every day to safeguard the public
19 from those who traffic illegal narcotics in our state. These awards emphasize
20 the ICP's commitment to aggressively combat drug trafficking and criminal
21 activities on Arkansas's interstates and highways",
22
23 NOW THEREFORE,
24 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE NINETY-FIFTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE
25 STATE OF ARKANSAS:
26
27 THAT the Senate recognize the Division of Arkansas State Police's
28 Interstate Criminal Patrol for winning top honors at the Gulf Coast High
29 Intensity Drug Trafficking Area Awards.
30
31 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED THAT upon adoption, a copy of this resolution be
32 presented to Colonel Mike Hagar by the Secretary of the Senate.
